entries.femaleVariant: Welcome back to our little oasis of elegance!
Inspire me.
No sequins.
A little quiet in here.
Agh, dunno... surprise me, inspire me. Fresh jacket, maybe, some new pants...?
entries.maleVariant: I dunno, uh... surprise me, inspire me. Uh, fresh jacket, maybe, some new pants...?

entries.femaleVariant: Or both? You are begging for a new do. Of course, nothing wrong with this look, but – fashion waits for no man!
Me, sequins? Gotta be kiddin'.
entries.maleVariant: Me, sequins? You gotta be kiddin'.

entries.femaleVariant: Now, just between the two of us – a touch of elegance can go a long way.
Lookin' a little empty these days.
What can I say? Jinguji is about quality, not quantity.
I'm sounding the alarm! Hold on!
Fuck, V! Get down! He's whacked!
Aaaugh!
Take 'im down! Now!
MaxTac... Be here in a moment. Hold him! Hold him till they get here!
Don't let him kill me!
MaxTac! Thank god!
Going in! Surround the target!
Move! Keep it up!
Eliminate him!
Target neutralized. Secure the witnesses!
You, over there! Statements, now!
Refusing to give a statement to a MaxTac officer may result in imprisonment.
You trying my patience here?
Sit. Hands where I can see 'em.
[Sit]
I said, sit.
Please, let's get this over with. I have to call the cleaners.
Melissa Rory, MaxTac senior officer. Please state your name and occupation.
Zane Jagger. I work for Jinguji, an oasis of elegance in--
V, merc. Occasional client of Zane's.
Checks out. Please describe what happened, starting from the moment of the attack.
I was just presenting V with a one-of-a-kind offer when I... I suddenly heard shouting from the street.
Then that... psychopath ran in. He killed... eh, fuck it – he slaughtered my guards!
I hit the alarm, V pinned the crazy bastard. Weren't for her... Wouldn't be anything left to clean up.
entries.maleVariant: I hit the alarm, V pinned the crazy bastard. Weren't for him... Wouldn't be anything left to clean up.

entries.femaleVariant: Hey, no problem. Was savin' my own ass, too.
entries.maleVariant: Eh, no problem. Was savin' my own ass, too.

entries.femaleVariant: Those mantis blades... Higurashis?
Situation resolved. Deactivate alarm.
Did you really have to kill him?
Hold up a sec... Your mantis blades – Higurashi 20-13's. Weren't those pulled off the market in '69?
Good eye. Had them installed years ago. They're very... precise.
They're my... reminder. When I see them, I see what they've sliced... Muscle, tendon, bone... even implants. Like a hot knife through butter.
You always just wipe 'em? Y'know, heard therapy can sometimes work--
Apprehending the target alive carries additional risk for bystanders. Rarely done. Very rarely.
Coroner's been notified. Be here any minute.
Jagger – this store is closed until the investigation is complete.
Nice work. You feel that back there? Feel his life leave his body?
Smith, report! How's it looking?
Two killed, two wounded inside the store. Six bodies on the street outside.
Where's the coroner?
Sitting in traffic. Be a little late.
Welcome to Jinguji.
Ah, look who it is! What a lovely surprise!
Uh, heh, all right? Whaddaya lookin' at?
entries.maleVariant: Uh, all right? Whaddaya lookin' at?

entries.femaleVariant: Now, what can I do for you today? Maybe a little upgrade, hm? Sequins are back, you know.
Well, on a more, ahem, generous frame, no – but with what you're working with, dear, they're perfect. You want to be shimra, you have to shine first.
If I can't convince you of that, I'll take it as a personal and professional failure. Someone like... like you...
Guards! Get the door! Hold him there!
I'd almost forgotten that pretty face. And what a pity that would be!
Just had to go play dutiful consumer in a corpo suit shop, didn't we?
Did you hear that...?
Talkin' to me?
Can hear you, remember?!
How could I forget.
Finally... Just have to mop this gunk up – we'll be back in business.
Please, sit down. Let's get this over with.
In accordance with Article 105 of the Cyberpsychosis Procedure Code, your statements will be recorded and retained.
Sorry. Habit.
Johnny Silverhand. Rock legend, voice in V's head, and also...
The fuck, Johnny...
Lemme pretend I exist sometimes, OK?
Was talking to Zane, when all of a sudden...
Zane was tryna sweet-talk me into some sparkly sequin shit. Psycho storms in, wipes the huscle.
Zane hits the alarm, locks us in with the fucker. Thanks, Zane.
Mr. Jagger followed the correct security protocol. He significantly reduced the assailant's range of effectiveness.
Yeah, noted... Played cat-and-mouse 'round the whole range of effectiveness before you lot showed up.
Anything else? Unusual behavior?
Don't drag this out!
But you're with the good guys now, right?
Rarely? More like never. How many psychos you save in your life?
Join us. Could use a few more like you.
I'll think about it.
Thanks, but no thanks.
Me, a cop? Heh, last time I wanted that, was pushin' six, maybe. Yeah I'll, uh, heh – I'll think about it.
Ooh, nice compliment, but uh, I'd feel like, I dunno... a merc in fuckin' sequins. Still might give it a think.
entries.maleVariant: Ooh, nice compliment, but I'd feel like, uh, dunno... a merc in fuckin' sequins? Still might give it a think.

entries.femaleVariant: You do that. You certainly got a gift.
Hey, V. Once we clean this place up, come by whenever you like. I'll hand-pick something special, just for you.
Thanks. Later, Zane.
What? That's it? No more questions?
Besides slicing and dicing my people and this store's reputation? No, nothing at all!
Thank you for your cooperation. That is all.
Recall they don't play well with neural processors – poking at a part of the prefronal cortex that shouldn't be poked at. Prolly would've bought a pair myself weren't for that.
entries.maleVariant: Recall they don't play well with neural processors – poking a part of the prefronal cortex that shouldn't be poked at. Prolly would've bought a pair myself weren't for that.

entries.femaleVariant: Huh. Thought MaxTac preferred Arasaka blades as their standard issue. But, well... seein' how you handled these wrist razors...
V, merc.
[Stand]
Nope. I'm not you.
Don't change the subject. You felt him die. Did you... like it? That split second when the blood still flows... but his light's gone out.
Well, the adrenaline's all right, but... don't think I share your level of enthusiasm.
If you're lookin' for a psycho soulmate – it ain't me, babe.
Maybe a little...
You love the hunt, love the kill. Don't matter if they're psychos or regular Joes.
Oh, we're not so different, you and I. Saw that look on your face right after. You can't hide it.
